Q: Explain the Architecture of Kubernetes

Answer (5-line interview style):

Kubernetes architecture consists of Control Plane components and Worker Node components.
The Control Plane manages cluster state using components like API Server, Scheduler, Controller Manager, and etcd.
Worker nodes run application containers and contain kubelet, kube-proxy, and container runtime.
The API Server acts as the central communication hub for all cluster operations.
This architecture enables Kubernetes to provide scalability, self-healing, and automated container orchestration.

Kubernetes Architecture Components (Explain if interviewer asks deeper)
